The paper deals with the identification of network services and applications on computing systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also presents an implementation of a fingerprinting tool, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and system programming (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mutation-based fuzzing, which is a technique commonly used in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
